---
/**
 * bloom-filters · 0003 · Figure 2 — "More items → more bits set → FP rate rises".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/bloom-filters/lessons/0003-failure-modes-and-lsm-reads.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup id="r2">). Lives as an .astro
 * component for the same reason as Fig1: raw inline SVG with kebab-case attributes
 * is unreliable inside MDX, but is plain HTML inside .astro. The source's SVG
 * comments are preserved as JSX comments inside <Fragment> would break flow, so
 * they are kept as plain HTML comments (valid inside an .astro SVG).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        viewBox="0 0 680 280"
        font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif"
    >
        <rect width="680" height="280" fill="#fffff8"></rect>
        <text x="340" y="26" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#0f4f47" font-weight="bold"
            >More items &#8594; more bits set &#8594; FP rate rises</text
        >
        <!-- axes -->
        <line x1="70" y1="220" x2="640" y2="220" stroke="#6b675f" stroke-width="1"></line>
        <line x1="70" y1="60" x2="70" y2="220" stroke="#6b675f" stroke-width="1"></line>
        <text x="355" y="262" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#6b675f"
            >load = items inserted &#247; design n</text
        >
        <text
            x="26"
            y="140"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="12"
            fill="#6b675f"
            transform="rotate(-90 26 140)">FP rate</text
        >
        <!-- bars: bits-set fraction (light) and FP rate (teal) at increasing load -->
        <!-- 0.5x -->
        <rect x="100" y="200" width="34" height="20" fill="#9fe7da" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect>
        <rect x="138" y="208" width="34" height="12" fill="#136f63" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect>
        <text x="135" y="236" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#3a372f">0.5&#215;</text>
        <!-- 1.0x design -->
        <rect x="220" y="178" width="34" height="42" fill="#9fe7da" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect>
        <rect x="258" y="196" width="34" height="24" fill="#136f63" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect>
        <text x="255" y="236" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#2f5d3a" font-weight="bold"
            >1&#215; design</text
        >
        <!-- 2x -->
        <rect x="340" y="142" width="34" height="78" fill="#9fe7da" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect>
        <rect x="378" y="158" width="34" height="62" fill="#136f63" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect>
        <text x="375" y="236" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#3a372f">2&#215;</text>
        <!-- 4x -->
        <rect x="460" y="92" width="34" height="128" fill="#9fe7da" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect>
        <rect x="498" y="100" width="34" height="120" fill="#136f63" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect>
        <text x="495" y="236" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#3a372f">4&#215;</text>
        <!-- legend -->
        <rect x="560" y="64" width="14" height="14" fill="#9fe7da" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect><text
            x="580"
            y="76"
            font-size="11"
            fill="#3a372f">bits set</text
        >
        <rect x="560" y="84" width="14" height="14" fill="#136f63" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect><text
            x="580"
            y="96"
            font-size="11"
            fill="#3a372f">FP rate</text
        >
        <text x="355" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#9a2417" font-weight="bold"
            >designed FP &#8594; quietly multiplied as it fills</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Past the design point, accuracy decays &#8212; the structure keeps answering, just worse<sup
            ><a href="#s2" id="r2">2</a></sup
        >.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
